# Example environment variables for local development.
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# DO NOT commit .env.local or real keys to git.

# TMDB API (required for metadata search, backdrops, and "剧照" stills in the Theater preview)
# You can use either:
# - A v3 API Key (the old style key string), or
# - A v4 Read Access Token (JWT starting with eyJ...) - recommended for new usage.
# Get it at: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api
#
# For the hosted closed-source version on CF Pages (your private deployment),
# set this as a secret Environment Variable in the Cloudflare dashboard (never commit the value).
# The /api/tmdb proxy will automatically use Bearer auth for v4 tokens or ?api_key= for v3.
TMDB_API_KEY=your_tmdb_v3_key_or_v4_read_access_token_here

# Optional: Cloudflare (only needed if running wrangler locally for preview/deploy)
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=...
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=...
